description: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of non-equivalent regular polygons with n+1 edges, one of which is rooted, which are dissected by non-intersecting diagonals into k regions, such that two such polygons are identified up to reflection along the rooted edge and twisting along the diagonals that does not affect the root edge (for 1 <= k <= n-1 and n >= 2).
